1
00:00:00,770 --> 00:00:02,510
What are you talking about?
That's ridiculous.

2
00:00:03,140 --> 00:00:06,980
The doctor distinctly told me
the baby died in my womb.

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:10,720
- How could a dead baby come back to life?
- Well...

4
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:14,190
I was just speaking hypothetically.
I said "what if."

5
00:00:14,190 --> 00:00:16,120
Why would you even say "what if?"

6
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:19,490
If my son had lived,
do you think I'd be going through this?

7
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,690
I would've taken over Dream ages ago.

8
00:00:22,290 --> 00:00:26,700
By now, I'd be at the very top of Dream
as the perfect queen.

9
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,140
But why are you asking about that
all of a sudden?

10
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:33,410
Don't tell me...

11
00:00:33,410 --> 00:00:34,410
What is it?

12
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:35,670
It can't be, can it?

13
00:00:35,740 --> 00:00:36,910
Tell me the truth.

14
00:00:40,610 --> 00:00:41,780
It's nothing.

15
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:43,920
Even if that child were alive,

16
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:48,750
you never would have made it
to the top of Dream.

17
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:50,790
- What?
- Have you forgotten?

18
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,720
Chairman Ma's biological daughter,
Ma Eun Hye.

19
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:55,290
Since Ma Eun Hye is actually Jung Suk Hee,

20
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:58,930
Chairman Ma would have named Jung Suk Hee
as his successor,

21
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,470
and you would've done far worse things
than you are now to stop that.

22
00:01:02,530 --> 00:01:04,600
How could a half-wit like Jung Suk Hee
become the successor?

23
00:01:04,670 --> 00:01:06,810
If your son had lived,

24
00:01:06,810 --> 00:01:08,710
you wouldn't have had to
steal one of the twins,

25
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:13,140
and Jung Suk Hee
wouldn't have gone half-wit, would she?

26
00:01:13,410 --> 00:01:15,450
She was smart enough
to pass the first round of the bar exam,

27
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,620
so she definitely would have taken
over Dream.

28
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:21,650
Why are you trying to ruin my mood
by dredging up the past?

29
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,960
Are you trying to get under my skin
on purpose?

30
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:27,460
You're around Han Young Ja too much.
Did her attitude rub off on you or what?

31
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:29,260
You're really pushing it.

32
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:32,130
No, that's not what I meant at all...

33
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:36,500
I apologize.

34
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:39,900
Anyway, once Chairman Ma
acknowledges Jung Suk Hee...

35
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,670
as his biological daughter,

36
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:44,440
it's a foregone conclusion
that we're finished.

37
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:48,050
What about Secretary Kim?

38
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:53,220
Are you watching the background check
Chairman Ma ordered him to do?

39
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:57,420
- Yes, I'm watching him like a hawk.
- Make sure you do.

40
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:02,060
Chairman Ma must never find out
Jung Suk Hee is his daughter, got it?

41
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:21,010
Why did you bring a box?
What do you even have to take with you?

42
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,620
Just leave empty-handed,
Kang Nam Bong, please.

43
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:26,950
I'm here for my books, that's all.
All right?

44
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:29,420
I'm not touching your things,
so don't worry.

45
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:30,860
Sit down for a second.

46
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,530
What's gotten into you?

47
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:39,130
- You want me to stay, is that it?
- Don't make me laugh.

48
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:42,730
- I want to talk about Baek Ho.
- Baek Ho?

49
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:49,610
Baek Ho's a grown man now.

50
00:02:50,010 --> 00:02:52,880
He's sharp and knows
how to take care of himself.

51
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:54,810
What's there to talk about
all of a sudden?

52
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:59,180
To be honest, I was hoping Baek Ho
would never search for his roots.

53
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:02,620
I don't know what their circumstances were
for abandoning a newborn,

54
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,590
but parents who would abandon
their own child...

55
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,560
You can imagine
what kind of people they must be.

56
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:12,730
- Look at Chae Hwa Young.
- For crying out loud.

57
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
What is it you're trying to say?

58
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:19,140
Did you just use Baek Ho as an excuse
to gossip about Chae Hwa Young?

59
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,940
For Baek Ho...

60
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:25,310
Let's help him find his birth parents.

61
00:03:28,550 --> 00:03:32,480
No, that's up to Baek Ho to do.

62
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,090
It's not our place
to take the lead on this.

63
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:37,990
He saw how much I was hurting...

64
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,430
because of Jun Ho.

65
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:45,900
That's why he wants
to find his birth parents,

66
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,270
but he's always walking on eggshells
around me.

67
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:55,570
So what are we supposed to do?
How do we find them?

68
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:57,540
With this.

69
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:05,350
You majored in industrial design,
so you're an expert on designs and logos.

70
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:09,190
You might even know the person
who designed this crest.

71
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,630
(Ma)

72
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:15,990
This isn't...

73
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,730
a typical run-of-the-mill metalwork.

74
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,330
It looks like a family crest.

75
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,900
I keep thinking that
wherever our Baek Ho came from...

76
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:28,770
wasn't exactly ordinary, don't you think?

77
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,710
(Ma)

78
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:39,950
Baek Ho, can you tell us the plan to make
Chae Hwa Young cough up her slush fund?

79
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,090
As part of this investment deal,

80
00:04:42,590 --> 00:04:44,960
if there are any legal
or ethical problems,

81
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:46,360
the contract is nullified,

82
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,290
plus, they’ll have to pay a penalty
three times the deposit.

83
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:52,860
But don't we have to put down a deposit
to sign a contract?

84
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:55,300
Do we even have that kind of money?

85
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:59,200
My legal name is Ma Seo Rin right now.

86
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:03,210
I'll take out a loan using the building
I got from Grandfather as collateral.

87
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,740
Do you really have to go that far?

88
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:08,410
If I want her to trust us,
this is a risk I have to take.

89
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:15,190
The deposit will be held in escrow,
and the penalty is three times that.

90
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:16,350
So if this works,

91
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:18,290
we can get our hands on...

92
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:19,490
Chae Hwa Young's
30-million-dollar slush fund.

93
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:25,660
Hello?

94
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,170
You're calling about the flyer?

95
00:05:30,170 --> 00:05:31,370
A flyer?

96
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:36,670
Grandfather put up flyers and banners
to find his biological daughter.

97
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:40,080
- They probably saw one and called.
- The Chairman's biological daughter?

98
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:44,120
- The Chairman lost his birth daughter?
- Yes.

99
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,650
If you just give me your name
and contact information,

100
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:48,720
Secretary Kim will get in touch with you.

101
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:50,890
Yes.

102
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,390
Okay.

103
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:55,730
That reminds me, Mom.
The police station called.

104
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:58,900
They said you made an appointment
to register your DNA but never showed up.

105
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,830
After Seo Rin's funeral,
we weren't in the right state of mind.

106
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,940
After all this time, I'm not sure
what the point is...

107
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,210
in looking for the parents
who abandoned me.

108
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:10,040
Then again, after seeing my grandfather,
I don't think that's necessarily true.

109
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:13,180
You don't know if they abandoned you
or if you were lost.

110
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,350
Let's go register yours, okay?

111
00:06:16,050 --> 00:06:17,050
I don't know.

112
00:06:19,020 --> 00:06:22,090
I need to go see the Chairman, Jang Mi.

113
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,460
I'll go with you, Baek Ho.

114
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:26,490
Mom, you should head back
to the hotel too.

115
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,790
Okay, I'll go there as Ali with Tommy.

116
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,700
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

117
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:38,270
(Diversified Revenue Portfolio)

118
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,010
I'm sorry, Hwa Young.

119
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:53,480
If I hadn't spirited away
Ma Dong Seok's true heir back then,

120
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:56,950
you never would have found our Jun Ho.

121
00:06:58,020 --> 00:06:59,020
My son.

122
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,830
My poor son, Jun Ho.

123
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,660
Even if I'm doomed for it,

124
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:09,270
I will make you the master of Dream Group.

125
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,010
Manager Lee, what are you doing
just standing there?

126
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:16,940
It's just...

127
00:07:18,910 --> 00:07:21,580
CEO Chae was worried about you.

128
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,720
She's worried about me,

129
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:27,450
but how could she cause such a scene
with Chairman Ali?

130
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:29,350
What's wrong with her?

131
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,960
- Why does she have to ruin everything?
- I think...

132
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,560
- it's because her anxiety is growing.
- We were so close.

133
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:41,570
We just had to sign papers in the suite,
and Hills Hotel would've been ours.

134
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:43,770
Why did she have to ruin everything
when we were so close?

135
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,870
She has been struggling lately,

136
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,240
with her hospital visit
for the grapefruit allergy.

137
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:52,110
So I think this might be a side effect
from all that.

138
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,240
A grapefruit allergy?

139
00:07:58,850 --> 00:08:00,890
Yes, Executive Director.
This is Kang Jun Ho.

140
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:04,220
General Manager Kang,
I'm afraid we can no longer wait for you.

141
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:07,860
Another buyer just came forward
who wants to buy Hills Hotel outright.

142
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:09,260
What?

143
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:11,630
What do you mean, a new buyer?

144
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:15,270
They've made an incredible offer,
and they have the cash to back it up.

145
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:18,570
Our board of directors is already leaning
in their favor.

146
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,200
So what's your move?

147
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:24,340
But we were already
in the middle of the deal.

148
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,980
Our financing is already secured.
We're just finalizing the details.

149
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,310
Please just give us a little more time.

150
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:33,750
(Tipster List)

151
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:40,590
Here, give this to Secretary Kim.
Have him run a preliminary check.

152
00:08:41,060 --> 00:08:42,060
Yes, sir.

153
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:46,160
Baek Ho and I will also screen the calls
from tipsters,

154
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:48,170
so you should just focus on your health,
Grandfather.

155
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,100
All right.

156
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:53,770
Well, we've put up banners
and handed out flyers.

157
00:08:54,370 --> 00:08:57,610
Surely, wherever Eun Hye is,
she's bound to see one of them.

158
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:59,980
I'm sure we'll find her soon.

159
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:03,650
We're looking into every Park Young Mi
in the country.

160
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:05,050
I'm sure we will find her.

161
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:06,520
Park Young Mi?

162
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:10,150
It's the name our Eun Hye was given
at the orphanage.

163
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:11,420
Park Young Mi.

164
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:17,560
- I have to take this. It's my brother.
- Go ahead.

165
00:09:21,530 --> 00:09:23,300
(Looking for Missing Person)

166
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,400
Sir.

167
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,870
There's something I was wondering about.

168
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:29,710
Ask away.

169
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:35,050
It's about this crest.

170
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:39,280
This? You mean our family crest?

171
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,690
If someone had an item
with this crest on it,

172
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,820
would that mean
they're part of your family?

173
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,420
Why do you ask?

174
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:49,960
I just feel like I've seen it
somewhere before.

175
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,600
A while back,

176
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:58,370
when CEO Chae said she was pregnant
with a son,

177
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:01,140
I sent her one as a gift back then.

178
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:02,970
To CEO Chae?

179
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,880
Chairman Ali.

180
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:12,680
I'm swallowing my pride
to beg for your forgiveness.

181
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,650
Please, I'm begging you.

182
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:18,760
- Please have the heart to forgive me.
- What is wrong with you? Are you insane?

183
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:21,360
- I don't get you at all.
- I've committed a terrible sin.

184
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:25,500
I will do anything to appease you,
Chairman Ali.

185
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:26,800
You mean that?

186
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,430
If you're truly sorry,

187
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,300
then okay, fine.

188
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:36,170
Pardon?

189
00:10:38,210 --> 00:10:42,710
You've got a great general manager.

190
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:46,080
What do you mean by that?

191
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,960
We'll talk details when we get there.

192
00:10:51,220 --> 00:10:54,790
First, I need to meet
your general manager.

193
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:56,330
Lead the way.

194
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,840
(Dream Hills Project Proposal)

195
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:13,610
When did he give this to her?

196
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,260
(Dream Hills Project Proposal)

197
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:32,530
Have you had a chance
to look over our proposal?

198
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:34,630
If we acquire Hills Hotel...

199
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:37,030
and get a license
for a casino resort there,

200
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,370
we can deliver a return
of ten times your investment.

201
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,870
Amazing.

202
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:45,380
Why didn't you tell me about this project?

203
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:48,350
I would've invested ages ago.

204
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,850
But the thing is...

205
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:54,350
I don't trust you, Mrs. Chae.

206
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,420
Are you emotionally unstable?

207
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:58,920
Insecure?

208
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:03,190
I was so shocked.
Why did you suddenly make such a scene?

209
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,200
Ma'am, that was just...

210
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:11,700
I've had things on my nerves lately,
and I wasn't myself.

211
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,840
I apologize.

212
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,610
I promise something so disgraceful
will never happen again.

213
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,640
Is that so? Okay.

214
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:20,140
Tommy, read it.

215
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:27,220
"The CEO of Dream Hotel
was caught on video abusing her power,"

216
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:29,420
"sparking major controversy."

217
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:32,790
This isn't a designated parking spot.

218
00:12:33,190 --> 00:12:34,960
Could you please move your car?

219
00:12:39,530 --> 00:12:41,300
Do you not know who I am?

220
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,200
This next article is a shocker.

221
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,900
It's about the death of Oh Bok Gil.

222
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:51,140
- Please give us a statement!
- CEO, are the murder allegations true?

223
00:12:51,140 --> 00:12:52,140
I'm innocent.

224
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:53,480
- Please tell us the truth.
- No!

225
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:55,780
- Are you admitting to the charges?
- I'm innocent! I said no!

226
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:58,680
- Just give us one comment, please.
- Do you admit the charges?

227
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:01,120
I was cleared of all those charges.

228
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:03,320
The case was closed
due to insufficient evidence.

229
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:06,690
That alone is a huge risk for me.

230
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,530
I was unfairly dragged into that.

231
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:11,000
But I'm completely in the clear now.

232
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:12,600
Then...

233
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,670
It never made the news,

234
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,970
- but I've heard even worse rumors.
- Chairman Ali.

235
00:13:20,270 --> 00:13:23,310
So, are we signing this contract or not?

236
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:28,110
- Tommy.
- Before we sign the contract,

237
00:13:28,710 --> 00:13:30,920
Chairman Ali would like to add one clause.

238
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,330
(Investment Agreement)

239
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,770
"Should there be further moral failings
on the part of the second party,"

240
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,800
"this contract will be
terminated immediately."

241
00:13:51,170 --> 00:13:53,140
"So if termination is..."

242
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:56,140
"due to Chae Hwa Young's personal,
moral, or legal misconduct..."

243
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:58,910
"damaging the company's image,"

244
00:13:58,910 --> 00:14:01,210
"this contract will be voided at once,"

245
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:02,810
"and the deposit paid..."

246
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,910
(Article 3: Morality and termination)

247
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,550
"must be returned threefold as a penalty."

248
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,650
Three times?

249
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,650
That's an incredibly harsh penalty.

250
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,260
The deposit I'm putting up
is ten million dollars.

251
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:15,630
If this contract is broken,
I'll incur massive losses.

252
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:18,460
I'm not in the business of losing money.

253
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:26,740
What? Mrs. Chae, got a guilty conscience?

254
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:30,870
Absolutely not.
I'm squeaky clean, of course.

255
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,510
Then why do you seem so flustered?

256
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,210
I'm not.

257
00:14:35,710 --> 00:14:38,220
It's such a large sum of money.

258
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:40,450
Actually, if that were to happen,

259
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:43,250
tell her the penalty has to be paid
by midnight the following day.

260
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,460
If something like that does happen,

261
00:14:48,730 --> 00:14:51,930
you must pay the penalty
by midnight the following day.

262
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:55,830
And if you fail to repay
the penalty by the deadline...

263
00:14:55,930 --> 00:14:58,070
Tell her you'll move on her real estate
and third-party receivables.

264
00:14:58,370 --> 00:15:00,140
They will be subject to immediate seizure,

265
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:03,340
and the debtor
cannot raise any objections.

266
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:07,810
You get it, Mrs. Chae?
Your real estate and third-party claims...

267
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,280
will be seized.

268
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:14,290
And the debtor
cannot raise any objections.

269
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:19,090
- Chairman, that's going too far.
- No.

270
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,660
Once this is notarized, it's ironclad.

271
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:25,600
It's all in the Korean Notary Public Act
and the Civil Enforcement Act.

272
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:28,630
Our smart General Manager Kang here
knows all about that, right?

273
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:31,340
This is just standard legal enforcement.

274
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:34,240
It's not like
it's ever going to happen anyway.

275
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,640
Right?

276
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:38,810
Of course. That's right.

277
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:41,150
It's not as if it will ever happen.

278
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,480
Okay, Tommy.

279
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:46,250
Draw up the contract, and call the notary.

280
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,580
Hold on a minute.

281
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,990
Are you sure
we should proceed this quickly?

282
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:54,690
Of course.
I'm a very busy woman. I have a lot to do.

283
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:01,730
(Loan agreement
Borrower: Ma Seo Rin)

284
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,870
I feel bad for Seo Rin,

285
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:06,970
but I have no choice
but to use her name for this.

286
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:11,510
I'll help you get your real name
back soon.

287
00:16:12,140 --> 00:16:13,210
Just hang in there until then.

288
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,080
To catch a tiger,

289
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,080
you have to walk into its den.

290
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:23,690
The ten million dollar preliminary deposit
will go into an escrow account,

291
00:16:23,890 --> 00:16:25,760
so we'll have no problem getting it back.

292
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:27,790
And we'll collect
the 30 million penalty, too?

293
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:29,390
That's right.

294
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:35,530
Hello, Mom.

295
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,400
Is that your mother, Baek Ho?

296
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,140
Can I talk to her for a second?

297
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:42,770
There's a favor I need to ask.

298
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:57,190
"Total operating capital for Dream Hills
is one billion dollars..."

299
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:58,190
(Investment Agreement)

300
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:03,630
"Hills Hotel’s sale proceeds
are 700 million dollars."

301
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:08,170
"Three hundred million for IT integration
and high-end brand remodeling."

302
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:10,600
"Total project cost
is one billion dollars."

303
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:12,740
This is exactly what was in the proposal
I gave you.

304
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:14,640
Let's review this one more time.

305
00:17:17,470 --> 00:17:19,740
"This contract goes beyond
a simple investment."

306
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:23,380
"It allows for compulsory execution
under the Civil Enforcement Act,"

307
00:17:23,650 --> 00:17:25,920
"and is contingent on the creation
of a notarized deed."

308
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:28,820
The moment you sign this yourself,
Mrs. Chae,

309
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:32,860
this deed will have the same legal force
as a final court judgment.

310
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,860
- You understand?
- Yes.

311
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:36,530
So, the only change
from the original draft is...

312
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:40,560
the addition of a clause
stating that we bear no moral risk.

313
00:17:40,730 --> 00:17:41,730
Sure.

314
00:17:41,730 --> 00:17:43,830
Mrs. Chae, do you agree?

315
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:46,100
That's right. One billion dollars.

316
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,510
Chae Hwa Young, one billion dollars.

317
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:50,510
Yes, I agree.

318
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:02,950
(Chae Hwa Young)

319
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:06,760
(Chae Hwa Young)

320
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:10,190
(Investor, Party A, Amira Ali,
Investee, Party B, Chae Hwa Young)

321
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,730
Once the wire transfer is confirmed,

322
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,640
we'll transfer the ten million dollars
from the TK Law Firm's escrow account.

323
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:27,980
The supporting documents came through.

324
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:29,710
The notarization number matches, too.

325
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:32,350
Now all you have to do is approve it.

326
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:34,320
Okay, one second.

327
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:39,490
Check if the ten million dollars came in,
Mrs. Chae.

328
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:47,760
It's here. The ten million dollars.

329
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,400
The deposited funds...

330
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,340
cannot be used for any purpose
other than the investment.

331
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:54,940
That goes without saying.

332
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:58,280
- We'll get right to work.
- Okay.

333
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:02,750
Then the deal is done.

334
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,520
Thank you, Chairman Ali.

335
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:07,890
Thank you.

336
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,320
Chae Hwa Young.

337
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:14,090
Congratulations on walking
right into the grave you dug for yourself.

338
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:18,360
Don't you think
that was a bit of a hasty decision?

339
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,530
It's fine.
Hills Hotel is going to be ours now.

340
00:19:24,130 --> 00:19:26,400
- But still...
- We're going to grow Dream Hills,

341
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:29,170
and then we'll start a full-scale takeover
of Dream.

342
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:32,380
We'll take down that old geezer,
Chairman Ma,

343
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:37,610
and merge Dream with Dream Hills
to become the best hotel in the world.

344
00:19:37,980 --> 00:19:42,020
By the way, how's your grapefruit allergy?
I didn't realize it was so severe.

345
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,260
- Did you hear that from Manager Lee?
- But...

346
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,390
Baek Ho has a grapefruit allergy, too.

347
00:19:48,830 --> 00:19:50,790
Is a grapefruit allergy
really that common?

348
00:19:50,860 --> 00:19:53,800
What? You're saying Kang Baek Ho
has a grapefruit allergy?

349
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,570
He won't even touch it.

350
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,200
Besides, Baek Ho was adopted, you know.

351
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:03,110
If you had given birth to another son
in the past and abandoned him,

352
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:06,510
I'd almost suspect
Kang Baek Ho was your son.

353
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:09,610
What are you talking about?
That's ridiculous.

354
00:20:09,950 --> 00:20:11,920
You are my only son.

355
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:12,980
Got it?

356
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,690
Yes.

357
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:17,220
Jun Ho, don't worry about anything else.

358
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:20,220
And just focus on
finalizing the Hills Hotel acquisition.

359
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:22,060
Understood.

360
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:31,770
Manager Lee just had to say that,
and it makes me feel uneasy.

361
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,000
What if...

362
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,810
What if, Hwa Young...

363
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:39,040
What if the son
you had with Ma Dong Seok...

364
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,180
didn't die?

365
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:43,610
What if he is alive somewhere?

366
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:46,080
No. That's impossible.

367
00:20:46,950 --> 00:20:48,090
He's dead.

368
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,040
Baek Ho, it's time to eat.

369
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:07,900
Where's Dad?

370
00:21:08,570 --> 00:21:09,810
He packed his bags and left.

371
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:14,380
He said he was getting a studio.
I guess he really did leave.

372
00:21:14,910 --> 00:21:16,480
Does that upset you?

373
00:21:17,950 --> 00:21:21,390
- He's your dad. It's understandable.
- No, Mom.

374
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,220
It's not like I'm a little kid anymore.

375
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:25,820
If I need to see him,
I'll just go visit him.

376
00:21:26,790 --> 00:21:29,960
More than anything, I just want you
to be happy, Mom.

377
00:21:30,890 --> 00:21:31,960
My dear son.

378
00:21:32,330 --> 00:21:35,970
With you by my side, I feel like
the richest person in the world.

379
00:21:37,230 --> 00:21:38,270
I'm starving.

380
00:21:38,270 --> 00:21:40,640
Okay, I made some stir-fried squid.

381
00:21:41,770 --> 00:21:44,210
Mom, you didn't forget
what Jang Mi asked for, did you?

382
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:46,310
How could I? It was Jang Mi who asked.

383
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:52,080
I'm about to acquire the Hills Hotel.

384
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:56,950
Once that happens, I, Chae Hwa Young,
will be back on top.

385
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,560
Thank you for your help.

386
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:03,130
That's right, Chae Hwa Young.

387
00:22:03,690 --> 00:22:05,660
You all thought I'd just curl up
and disappear, didn't you?

388
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:10,170
I'm about to spread my wings and soar,
so just you wait.

389
00:22:17,740 --> 00:22:20,780
- Have you lost your mind?
- Your son, Kang Jun Ho...

390
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:22,950
Wasn't it enough
that you made me raise him?

391
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:25,620
And now you're living
with my husband and Jun Ho together...

392
00:22:26,020 --> 00:22:27,420
as a family?

393
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,820
What is going on?

394
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,020
Chairman Ali.

395
00:22:32,690 --> 00:22:35,130
I came here hoping we could celebrate
our contract with a drink,

396
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:37,460
but what did I just walk in on?

397
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:40,260
You. Say that again.
What did you just say?

398
00:22:40,530 --> 00:22:41,830
I don't know who you are,

399
00:22:43,130 --> 00:22:44,840
but you shouldn't do business
with this woman.

400
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:47,600
That's not true.

401
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:49,170
Han Young Ja, are you insane?

402
00:22:49,540 --> 00:22:52,740
How dare you cause a scene here?
Get out! I said, get out!

403
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:54,640
Who do you think you're pushing?

404
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:58,120
You want a piece of me?
Let's see who's tougher.

405
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:02,390
- Manager Lee, get her out of here.
- How dare you...

406
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:12,060
Is this the Angel Forest Orphanage?

407
00:23:13,430 --> 00:23:16,670
- I'm looking for someone.
- Yes, how can I help you?

408
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:18,370
About 30 years ago,

409
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,900
a child was left at your front door...

410
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,440
No...

411
00:23:24,610 --> 00:23:26,240
I'm the one who abandoned that child.

412
00:23:26,510 --> 00:23:28,610
Was it a girl or a boy?

413
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:31,010
A boy.

414
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:37,150
Chae Hwa Young, do you want me
to bury you in adultery lawsuits?

415
00:23:37,550 --> 00:23:39,360
Didn't I tell you that
if you ever saw my husband again,

416
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:43,590
I'd sue you every single time?

417
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:47,230
I haven't even seen Professor Kang lately.
What's this about moving in together?

418
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:50,600
- That's not true.
- An adultery lawsuit?

419
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:52,600
Oh my gosh.

420
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:56,310
Chairman Ali, that's not true.
It's a misunderstanding.

421
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:59,410
A misunderstanding, my foot!
I caught you two in each other's arms...

422
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:02,550
and professing your love for each other
in this room.

423
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:03,850
How is that a misunderstanding?

424
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:06,150
Chairman Ali, that's not what happened.

425
00:24:10,190 --> 00:24:13,020
I have piles of photographic evidence
right here.

426
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:14,760
I even have the statements...

427
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:17,290
for the damages she paid me
from the adultery lawsuit.

428
00:24:17,490 --> 00:24:20,230
When it comes to evidence,
I have more than enough.

429
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,170
As it just so happens,

430
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:27,840
I'm a divorce lawyer,
so I've been carefully gathering evidence.

431
00:24:28,570 --> 00:24:30,940
You're driving me nuts!
Why are you here ruining everything?

432
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:34,010
Do you want to know why
I haven't divorced him yet?

433
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:37,510
I was going to strip you two bare...

434
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:39,750
and throw you out on the street
with nothing.

435
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:42,790
I just needed a little more time
to do that.

436
00:24:43,090 --> 00:24:46,460
You couldn't wait and moved in together?

437
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:47,890
Stop!

438
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:51,490
So you're a homewrecker?

439
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:56,030
- That's not true. It's unfair.
- "Unfair?"

440
00:24:56,430 --> 00:24:58,640
Unfair? Listen to you!

441
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:02,910
Who's the one being treated unfairly here?
How dare a homewrecker play the victim?

442
00:25:02,970 --> 00:25:04,980
Let go of me!

443
00:25:05,540 --> 00:25:06,540
Mom.

444
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,080
How dare you...

445
00:25:10,350 --> 00:25:11,680
You're just a homewrecker.

446
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,780
What gives you the right
to lay a hand on me?

447
00:25:14,150 --> 00:25:16,150
You're the one who grabbed my hair first!

448
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:19,220
Manager Lee, get them out of here!

449
00:25:20,090 --> 00:25:22,790
Chairman Ali, please, just hear me out.

450
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:24,790
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

451
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,500
Let's go.

452
00:25:34,870 --> 00:25:37,310
Chairman Ali,
allow me to escort you to the suite.

453
00:25:38,210 --> 00:25:39,440
Wait.

454
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:43,150
I need to talk to Mrs. Chae.

455
00:25:43,650 --> 00:25:45,220
Director Ma, you can go on ahead.

456
00:25:45,450 --> 00:25:48,890
Chae Hwa Young.
Chairman Ali is a VVIP guest of our hotel.

457
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,890
So make sure
you do nothing to displease her.

458
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:03,070
Thank you so much for doing me this favor.

459
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,970
Actually, I should be thanking
you and Baek Ho.

460
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:10,240
I feel so much better
after letting Chae Hwa Young have it.

461
00:26:10,310 --> 00:26:12,710
It feels like a ten-year weight
has finally been lifted.

462
00:26:13,810 --> 00:26:15,010
Han Young Ja!

463
00:26:16,750 --> 00:26:18,050
- Hey.
- Right.

464
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:24,690
Tommy.

465
00:26:25,290 --> 00:26:27,720
Void the contract right now.

466
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:33,360
Chairman Ali, you can't do this.

467
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:35,800
Please, just listen to me.

468
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,870
Give me back
my ten million dollar deposit,

469
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,800
plus a 30-million-dollar penalty,
three times the deposit.

470
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,770
Wire it to my account right now.

471
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:45,510
Or else I'm having you arrested for fraud.

472
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:47,740
Thirty million dollars?

473
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:50,910
- You can't do this, Chairman.
- I can't?

474
00:26:52,550 --> 00:26:54,320
Did you forget this was notarized?

475
00:26:58,490 --> 00:27:01,730
"Notarization certificate number
2026 D742."

476
00:27:02,260 --> 00:27:04,960
"This certifies the notarization
for this contract."

477
00:27:05,430 --> 00:27:07,130
"As such,
this document is state-guaranteed,"

478
00:27:09,430 --> 00:27:11,670
"making it legally enforceable."

479
00:27:15,940 --> 00:27:16,940
Right here.

480
00:27:17,810 --> 00:27:21,210
I have concrete proof.
As stipulated in the contract,

481
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:23,980
you can either pay
the triple penalty and cancel,

482
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:28,220
or I can have all your assets seized,
as per the notarized document.

483
00:27:28,490 --> 00:27:29,490
Choose.

484
00:27:31,820 --> 00:27:34,960
- That's impossible.
- "Impossible" is not an option. What now?

485
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:37,360
Call Chairman Ma right now.

486
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:42,070
If you can't pay the penalty fee,
I'm seizing all of your shares.

487
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,270
The penalty fee...

488
00:27:47,470 --> 00:27:48,970
I'll pay it.

489
00:27:50,010 --> 00:27:51,040
Now.

490
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:53,510
Manager Lee.

491
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,780
Withdraw the funds
from my Swiss account...

492
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:00,620
and transfer them to the escrow account
provided by Chairman Ali.

493
00:28:03,090 --> 00:28:06,620
Wire the 30 million dollars now.

494
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,860
Chae Hwa Young,
are you really crying over this?

495
00:28:16,170 --> 00:28:17,800
I lost my daughter.

496
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,770
And you're crying just because
you lost some money?

497
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,540
You wretched woman.

498
00:28:24,270 --> 00:28:26,610
From now on,
I'll make you shed tears of blood.

499
00:28:58,140 --> 00:28:59,810
(The First Man)

500
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:02,680
Does CEO Chae by any chance
have a golden toad?

501
00:29:02,810 --> 00:29:05,420
I heard it's supposed to be stamped
with the Chairman's family crest.

502
00:29:05,850 --> 00:29:09,790
Don't you think you're getting off easy
for all the pain you've caused?

503
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:12,420
If you've got any fight left in you,
save it.

504
00:29:12,690 --> 00:29:14,260
This is just the beginning.

505
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:18,460
So you're aging up Ma Eun Hye's photo
to predict how she looks in her 50s?

506
00:29:18,630 --> 00:29:20,630
Change the face in that sketch to mine.

507
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,770
I'll become Chairman Ma's real daughter.
I'll become Ma Eun Hye.

508
00:29:25,470 --> 00:29:27,470
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
